    {
      "id": "981bb5a1f39b4b5260b53808f025506db71d530f",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2014-10-12 02:12:02.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nI don't think we are landing patches to b2_6 because we aren't planning in making any releases there after 2.6.0.\n\nIs it possible to avoid this problem on master somehow?  \n\nOleg, what are your thoughts on this? Would we land patches into b2_6 to avoid making the code on master more ugly to workaround a downgrade problem?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "eee5a1ab5e6cbdd4c56ac7c77de92bc72c6d19ee",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 3,
        "name": "Fan Yong",
        "email": "fan.yong@intel.com",
        "username": "nasf",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2014-10-12 02:19:37.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nIf we want to avoid such issue from master, we can use another new XATTR_NAME (XATTR_NAME_LFSCK_NAMESPACE_NEW) for the namespace LFSCK tracing file. Then when downgrade to Lustre-2.6 or Lustre-2.5, the old LFSCK will try to load the old XATTR_NAME (XATTR_NAME_LFSCK_NAMESPACE), then will get -ENODATA, then the existing logic can handle it.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "4dfb63871f89996ede1fad935daea382a0075fd4",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 403,
        "name": "Autotest",
        "email": "autotest@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "autotest",
        "tags": [
          "SERVICE_USER"
        ]
      },
      "date": "2014-10-12 03:23:48.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nShadow Autotest2 started enforced review session.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "cf080cd07618ed3d27096eaa7f63145d02e4a3af",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 403,
        "name": "Autotest",
        "email": "autotest@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "autotest",
        "tags": [
          "SERVICE_USER"
        ]
      },
      "date": "2014-10-12 05:24:29.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nShadow Autotest2 started optional review-zfs session.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "1d06983a3359a1c287ee9783afbc418f0ea552f1",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2014-10-12 07:02:31.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nThat would probably be better than having to patch all of the released versions of Lustre. Of course, the master code should still be fixed to avoid this problem in the future by deleting the xattr if it doesn't understand it, and just start LFSCK again. Also, it should try to delete the old xattr to avoid leaking space since there may only be 4KB of xattr  space on the inode.  \n\nThe code to delete the old xattr should be under a check like:\n\n #ifdef LUSTRE_VERSION_CODE < OBD_OCD_VERSION(3,2,53)\n\nSo that it stops trying to remove the old xattr and that compatibility code can itself be removed.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "2539aed97c99301b0a51f9af1a6c5afa989db98a",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 3,
        "name": "Fan Yong",
        "email": "fan.yong@intel.com",
        "username": "nasf",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2014-10-12 10:06:52.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nSince then, both the patch for b2_6 and the patch for b2_5 are unnecessary. I will make patch on master directly to fix the issues as suggested.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
