        "subject": "LU-5707 lfsck: recreate LFSCK tracing file for load failure",
        "message": "LU-5707 lfsck: recreate LFSCK tracing file for load failure\n\nThe extended attribute XATTR_NAME_LFSCK_NAMESPACE for namespace\nLFSCK tracing file is enlarged since Lustre-2.7. When downgrade\nfrom Lustre-2.7, the old MDS will get -ERANGE when loads the\nXATTR_NAME_LFSCK_NAMESPACE extended attribute from the new\nformatted on-disk namespace LFSCK tracing file. Under such case,\nthe LFSCK should not return failure, instead, it can recreate the\nXATTR_NAME_LFSCK_NAMESPACE EA as initialization case.\n\nMore further, if the LFSCK failed to load tracing file, it is\nunncessary to fail the whole LFSCK, instead, just recreate the\ntracing file.\n\nSigned-off-by: Fan Yong <fan.yong@intel.com>\nChange-Id: Ifffd8fc89ff74fd2afbd7bb2df1da33dde52d7c9\n"
      },
